List of moves

Sign in to edit
  • View history
  • Talk (0)

This is a list of all the moves Pokémon can learn. These are displayed in alphabetical order.

Until Generation III the physical and special categories were classified by type, not by move. The only ones that were according to the move were the ones classified in other. They were ordered this way:

Category Type of moves
- - - - - - - -
- - - - - - -
Varies according to the move

From Generation IV onward, each category depends on the move, not on the type. The ones that were classified as other keep their condition, however.

A[]

Name Type Category Contest Japanese In-game description
Absorb すいとる A nutrient-draining attack. The user's HP is restored by half the damage taken by the target.
Acid ようかいえき The opposing Pokémon are attacked with a spray of harsh acid. This may also lower their Sp. Def stats.
Acid Armor とける The user alters its cellular structure to liquefy itself, sharply raising its Defense stat.
Acid Spray アシッドボム The user spits fluid that works to melt the target. This harshly lowers the target's Sp. Def stat.
Acrobatics アクロバット The user nimbly strikes the target. If the user is not holding an item, this attack inflicts massive damage.
Acupressure [1] つぼをつく The user applies pressure to stress points, sharply boosting one of its stats or its allies' stats.
Aerial Ace つばめがえし The user confounds the target with speed, then slashes. This attack never misses.
Aeroblast エアロブラスト A vortex of air is shot at the target to inflict damage. Critical hits land more easily.
After You おさきにどうぞ The user helps the target and makes it use its move right after the user.
Agility こうそくいどう The user relaxes and lightens its body to move faster. This sharply raises the Speed stat.
Air Cutter エアカッター The user launches razor-like wind to slash the opposing Pokémon. Critical hits land more easily.
Air Slash エアスラッシュ The user attacks with a blade of air that slices even the sky. This may also make the target flinch.
Ally Switch サイドチェンジ The user teleports using a strange power and switches places with one of its allies.
Amnesia ドわすれ The user temporarily empties its mind to forget its concerns. This sharply raises the user's Sp. Def stat.
Ancient Power

[2]

げんしのちから The user attacks with a prehistoric power. This may also raise all the user's stats at once.
Aqua Jet [3] アクアジェット The user lunges at the target at a speed that makes it almost invisible. This move always goes first.
Aqua Ring アクアリング The user envelops itself in a veil made of water. It regains some HP every turn.
Aqua Tail [4] アクアテール The user attacks by swinging its tail as if it were a vicious wave in a raging storm.
Arm Thrust つっぱり The user looses a flurry of open-palmed arm thrusts that hit two to five times in a row.
Aromatherapy アロマセラピー The user releases a soothing scent that heals all status conditions affecting the user's party.
Assist ねこのて The user hurriedly and randomly uses a move among those known by other Pokémon in the party.
Assurance [3] ダメおし If the target has already taken some damage in the same turn, this attack's power is doubled.
Astonish [5] おどろかす The user attacks the target while shouting in a startling fashion. This may also make the target flinch.
Attack Order こうげきしれい The user calls out its underlings to pummel the target. Critical hits land more easily.
Attract メロメロ If it is the opposite gender of the user, the target becomes infatuated and less likely to attack.
Aura Sphere はどうだん The user looses a blast of aura power from deep within its body at the target. This attack never misses.
Aurora Beam オーロラビーム The target is hit with a rainbow-colored beam. This may also lower the target's Attack stat.
Autotomize ボディパージ The user sheds part of its body to make itself lighter and sharply raise its Speed stat.
Avalanche [1] ゆきなだれ An attack move that inflicts double the damage if the user has been hurt by the target in the same turn.

B[]

Name Type Category Contest Japanese In-game description
Baby-Doll Eyes つぶらなひとみ The user stares at the target with its baby-doll eyes, which lowers its Attack stat. This move always goes first.
Barrage [6] たまなげ Round objects are hurled at the target to strike two to five times in a row.
Barrier バリアー The user throws up a sturdy wall that sharply raises its Defense stat.
Baton Pass バトンタッチ The user switches places with a party Pokémon in waiting and passes along any stat changes.
Beat Up ふくろだたき The user gets all party Pokémon to attack the target. The more party Pokémon, the greater the number of attacks.
Belly Drum はらだいこ The user maximizes its Attack stat in exchange for HP equal to half its max HP.
Bestow ギフトパス The user passes its held item to the target when the target isn't holding an item.
Bide がまん The user endures attacks for two turns, then strikes back to cause double the damage taken.
Bind しめつける Things such as long bodies or tentacles are used to bind and squeeze the target for four to five turns.
Bite [7] かみつく The target is bitten with viciously sharp fangs. This may also make the target flinch.
Blast Burn ブラストバーン The target is razed by a fiery explosion. The user can't move on the next turn.
Blaze Kick [3] ブレイズキック The user launches a kick that lands a critical hit more easily. This may also leave the target with a burn.
Blizzard ふぶき A howling blizzard is summoned to strike opposing Pokémon. This may also leave the opposing Pokémon frozen.
Block とおせんぼう The user blocks the target's way with arms spread wide to prevent escape.
Blue Flare あおいほのお The user attacks by engulfing the target in an intense, yet beautiful, blue flame. This may also leave the target with a burn.
Body Slam のしかかり The user drops onto the target with its full body weight. This may also leave the target with paralysis.
Bolt Strike らいげき The user surrounds itself with a great amount of electricity and charges its target. This may also leave the target with paralysis.
Bone Club ホネこんぼう The user clubs the target with a bone. This may also make the target flinch.
Bone Rush ボーンラッシュ The user strikes the target with a hard bone two to five times in a row.
Bonemerang ホネブーメラン The user throws the bone it holds. The bone loops to hit the target twice, coming and going.
Boomburst ばくおんぱ The user attacks everything around it with the destructive power of a terrible, explosive sound.
Bounce とびはねる The user bounces up high, then drops on the target on the second turn. This may also leave the target with paralysis.
Brave Bird [4] ブレイブバード The user tucks in its wings and charges from a low altitude. This also damages the user quite a lot.
Brick Break かわらわり The user attacks with a swift chop. It can also break barriers, such as Light Screen and Reflect.
Brine [5] しおみず If the target's HP is half or less, this attack will hit with double the power.
Bubble あわ A spray of countless bubbles is jetted at the opposing Pokémon. This may also lower their Speed stats.
Bubble Beam

[8]

バブルこうせん A spray of bubbles is forcefully ejected at the target. This may also lower its Speed stat.
Bug Bite [6] むしくい The user bites the target. If the target is holding a Berry, the user eats it and gains its effect.
Bug Buzz [4] むしのさざめき The user vibrates its wings to generate a damaging sound wave. This may also lower the target's Sp. Def stat.
Bulk Up [3] ビルドアップ The user tenses its muscles to bulk up its body, raising both its Attack and Defense stats.
Bulldoze じならし The user strikes everything around it by stomping down on the ground. This lowers the Speed stat of those hit.
Bullet Punch [5] バレットパンチ The user strikes the target with tough punches as fast as bullets. This move always goes first.
Bullet Seed タネマシンガン The user forcefully shoots seeds at the target two to five times in a row.

C[]

Name Type Category Contest Japanese In-game description
Calm Mind めいそう The user quietly focuses its mind and calms its spirit to raise its Sp. Atk and Sp. Def stats.
Camouflage ほごしょく The user's type is changed depending on its environment, such as at water's edge, in grass, or in a cave.
Captivate [3] ゆうわく If any opposing Pokémon is the opposite gender of the user, it is charmed, which harshly lowers its Sp. Atk stat.
Celebrate おいわい The Pokémon congratulates you on your special day!
Charge じゅうでん The user boosts the power of the Electric move it uses on the next turn. This also raises the user's Sp. Def stat.
Charge Beam チャージビーム The user attacks with an electric charge. The user may use any remaining electricity to raise its Sp. Atk stat.
Charm [9] あまえる The user gazes at the target rather charmingly, making it less wary. This harshly lowers its Attack stat.
Chatter [5] おしゃべり The user attacks the target with sound waves of deafening chatter. This confuses the target.
Chip Away なしくずし Looking for an opening, the user strikes consistently. The target's stat changes don't affect this attack's damage.
Circle Throw ともえなげ The target is thrown, and a different Pokémon is dragged out. In the wild, this ends a battle against a single Pokémon.
Clamp からではさむ The target is clamped and squeezed by the user's very thick and sturdy shell for four to five turns.
Clear Smog クリアスモッグ The user attacks by throwing a clump of special mud. All stat changes are returned to normal.
Close Combat [5] インファイト The user fights the target up close without guarding itself. This also lowers the user's Defense and Sp. Def stats.
Coil とぐろをまく The user coils up and concentrates. This raises its Attack and Defense stats as well as its accuracy.
Comet Punch れんぞくパンチ The target is hit with a flurry of punches that strike two to five times in a row.
Confide ないしょばなし The user tells the target a secret, and the target loses its ability to concentrate. This lowers the target's Sp. Atk. stat.
Confuse Ray あやしいひかり The target is exposed to a sinister ray that triggers confusion.
Confusion ねんりき The target is hit by a weak telekinetic force. This may also confuse the target.
Constrict からみつく The target is attacked with long, creeping tentacles or vines. This may also lower the target's Speed stat.
Conversion テクスチャー The user changes its type to become the same type as the move at the top of the list of moves it knows.
Conversion 2

[10]

テクスチャー２ The user changes its type to make itself resistant to the type of the attack the opponent used last.
Copycat [1] まねっこ The user mimics the move used immediately before it. The move fails if no other move has been used yet.
Cosmic Power [1] コスモパワー The user absorbs a mystical power from the space to raise its Defense and Sp. Def stats.
Cotton Guard コットンガード The user protects itself by wrapping its body in soft cotton, which drastically raises the user's Defense stat.
Cotton Spore わたほうし The user releases cotton-like spores that cling to the opposing Pokémon, which harshly lowers their Speed stats.
Counter カウンター A retaliation move that counters any physical attack, inflicting double the damage taken.
Covet ほしがる The user endearingly approaches the target, then steals the target's held item.
Crabhammer クラブハンマー The target is hammered with a large pincer. Critical hits land more easily.
Crafty Shield トリックガード The user protects itself and its allies from status moves with a mysterious power. This does not stop moves that do damage.
Cross Chop クロスチョップ The user delivers a double chop with its forearms crossed. Critical hits land more easily.
Cross Poison クロスポイズン A slashing attack with a poisonous blade that may also poison the target. Critical hits land more easily.
Crunch かみくだく The user crunches up the target with sharp fangs. This may also lower the target's Defense stat.
Crush Claw ブレイククロー The user slashes the target with hard and sharp claws. This may also lower the target's Defense.
Crush Grip にぎりつぶす The target is crushed with great force. The more HP the target has left, the greater this move's power.
Curse [11] のろい A move that works differently for the Ghost type than for all other types.
Cut いあいぎり The target is cut with a scythe or claw. This can also be used to cut down thin trees.

D[]

Name Type Category Contest Japanese In-game description
Dark Pulse あくのはどう The user releases a horrible aura imbued with dark thoughts. This may also make the target flinch.
Dark Void ダークホール Opposing Pokémon are dragged into a world of total darkness that makes them sleep.
Dazzling Gleam マジカルシャイン The user damages opposing Pokémon by emitting a powerful flash.
Defend Order ぼうぎょしれい The user calls out its underlings to shield its body, raising its Defense and Sp. Def stats.
Defense Curl まるくなる The user curls up to conceal weak spots and raise its Defense stat.
Defog [3] きりばらい A strong wind blows away the target's barriers such as Reflect or Light Screen. This also lowers the target's evasiveness.
Destiny Bond みちづれ When this move is used, if the user faints, the Pokémon that landed the knockout hit also faints.
Detect みきり Enables the user to evade all attacks. Its chance of failing rises if it is used in succession.
Diamond Storm ダイヤストーム The user whips up a storm of diamonds to damage opposing Pokémon. This may also raise the user's Defense stat.
Dig [5] あなをほる The user burrows, then attacks on the next turn. It can also be used to exit dungeons.
Disable かなしばり For four turns, this move prevents the target from using the move it last used.
Disarming Voice チャームボイス Letting out a charming cry, the user does emotional damage to opposing Pokémon. This attack never misses.
Discharge [1] ほうでん The user strikes everything around it by letting loose a flare of electricity. This may also cause paralysis.
Dive ダイビング Diving on the first turn, the user floats up and attacks on the next turn. It can be used to dive deep in the ocean.
Dizzy Punch [1] ピヨピヨパンチ The target is hit with rhythmically launched punches. This may also leave the target confused.
Doom Desire [1] はめつのねがい Two turns after this move is used, the user blasts the target with a concentrated bundle of light.
Double Hit [5] ダブルアタック The user slams the target with a long tail, vines, or a tentacle. The target is hit twice in a row.
Double Kick にどげり The target is quickly kicked twice in succession using both feet.
Double Slap

[12]

[6] おうふくビンタ The target is slapped repeatedly, back and forth, two to five times in a row.
Double Team かげぶんしん By moving rapidly, the user makes illusory copies of itself to raise its evasiveness.
Double-Edge すてみタックル A reckless, life-risking tackle. This also damages the user quite a lot.
Draco Meteor [5] りゅうせいぐん Comets are summoned down from the sky onto the target. The attack's recoil harshly lowers the user's Special Attack stat.
Dragon Ascent ガリョウテンセイ After soaring upward, the user attacks its target by dropping out of the sky at high speeds, although it lowers its own Defense and Sp. Def in the process.
Dragon Breath りゅうのいぶき The user exhales a mighty gust that inflicts damage. This may also leave the target with paralysis.
Dragon Claw ドラゴンクロー The user slashes the target with huge, sharp claws.
Dragon Dance りゅうのまい The user vigorously performs a mystic, powerful dance that boosts its Attack and Speed stats.
Dragon Pulse [5] りゅうのはどう The target is attacked with a shock wave generated by the user's gaping mouth.
Dragon Rage りゅうのいかり This attack hits the target with a shock wave of pure rage. This attack always inflicts 40 HP damage.
Dragon Rush [6] ドラゴンダイブ The user tackles the target while exhibiting overwhelming menace. This may also make the target flinch.
Dragon Tail ドラゴンテール The target is knocked away, and a different Pokémon is dragged out. In the wild, this ends a battle against a single Pokémon.
Drain Punch [3] ドレインパンチ An energy-draining punch. The user's HP is restored by half the damage taken by the target.
Draining Kiss ドレインキッス The user steals the target's energy with a kiss. The user's HP is restored by over half of the damage taken by the target.
Dream Eater ゆめくい The user eats the dreams of a sleeping target. It absorbs half the damage caused to heal its own HP.
Drill Peck ドリルくちばし A corkscrewing attack with a sharp beak acting as a drill.
Drill Run ドリルライナー The user crashes into its target while rotating its body like a drill. Critical hits land more easily.
Dual Chop ダブルチョップ The user attacks its target by hitting it with brutal strikes. The target is hit twice in a row.
Dynamic Punch ばくれつパンチ The user punches the target with full, concentrated power. This confuses the target if it hits.

E[]

Name Type Category Contest Japanese In-game description
Earth Power [5] だいちのちから The user makes the ground under the target erupt with power. This may also lower the target's Sp. Def.
Earthquake じしん The user sets off an earthquake that strikes every Pokémon around it.
Echoed Voice エコーボイス The user attacks the target with an echoing voice. If this move is used every turn, it does greater damage.
Eerie Impulse かいでんぱ The user's body generates an eerie impulse. Exposing the target to it harshly lowers the target's Sp. Atk stat.
Egg Bomb [6] タマゴばくだん A large egg is hurled at the target with maximum force to inflict damage.
Electric Terrain エレキフィールド The user electrifies the ground under everyone's feet for five turns. Pokémon on the ground no longer fall asleep.
Electrify そうでん If the target is electrified before it uses a move during that turn, the target's move becomes Electric type.
Electro Ball エレキボール The user hurls an electric orb at the target. The faster the user is than the target, the greater the move's power.
Electroweb エレキネット The user attacks and captures opposing Pokémon by using an electric net. This lowers their Speed stat.
Embargo [4] さしおさえ This move prevents the target from using its held item. Its Trainer is also prevented from using items on it.
Ember [3] ひのこ The target is attacked with small flames. This may also leave the target with a burn.
Encore アンコール The user compels the target to keep using only the move it last used for three turns.
Endeavor がむしゃら An attack move that cuts down the target's HP to equal the user's HP.
Endure こらえる The user endures any attack with at least 1 HP. Its chance of failing rises if it is used in succession.
Energy Ball エナジーボール The user draws power from nature and fires it at the target. This may also lower the target's Sp. Def.
Entrainment なかまづくり The user dances with an odd rhythm that compels the target to mimic it, making the target's Ability the same as the user's.
Eruption ふんか The user attacks opposing Pokémon with explosive fury. The lower the user's HP, the lower the move's power.
Explosion だいばくはつ The user attacks everything around it by causing a tremendous explosion. The user faints upon using this move.
Extrasensory じんつうりき The user attacks with an odd, unseeable power. This may also make the target flinch.
Extreme Speed

[13]

しんそく The user charges the target at blinding speed. This move always goes first.

F[]

Name Type Category Contest Japanese In-game description
Facade からげんき An attack move that doubles its power if the user is poisoned, is burned, or has paralysis.
Fairy Lock フェアリーロック By locking down the battlefield, the user keeps all Pokémon from fleeing during the next turn.
Fairy Wind ようせいのかぜ The user stirs up a fairy wind and strikes the target with it.
Fake Out ねこだまし An attack that hits first and makes the target flinch. It only works the first turn the user is in battle.
Fake Tears [5] うそなき The user feigns crying to fluster the target, harshly lowering its Sp. Def stat.
False Swipe みねうち A restrained attack that prevents the target from fainting. The target is left with at least 1 HP.
Feather Dance

[14]

フェザーダンス The user covers the target's body with a mass of down that harshly lowers its Attack stat.
Feint [3] フェイント An attack that hits a target using Protect or Detect. This also lifts the effects of those moves.
Feint Attack だましうち The user approaches the target disarmingly, then throws a sucker punch. This attack never misses.
Fell Stinger とどめばり When the user knocks out a target with this move, the user's Attack stat rises sharply.
Fiery Dance ほのおのまい Cloaked in flames, the user dances and flaps its wings. This may also raise the user's Sp. Atk stat.
Final Gambit いのちがけ The user risks everything to attack its target. The user faints but does damage equal to its HP.
Fire Blast だいもんじ The target is attacked with an intense blast of all-consuming fire. This may also leave the target with a burn.
Fire Fang [3] ほのおのキバ The user bites with flame-cloaked fangs. This may also make the target flinch or leave it with a burn.
Fire Pledge ほのおのちかい A column of fire hits opposing Pokémon. When used with its grass equivalent, its damage increases and a vast sea of fire appears.
Fire Punch [3] ほのおのパンチ The target is punched with a fiery fist. This may also leave the target with a burn.
Fire Spin ほのおのうず The target becomes trapped within a fierce vortex of fire that rages for four to five turns.
Fissure じわれ The user opens up a fissure in the ground and drops the target in. The target faints instantly if this attack hits.
Flail じたばた The user flails about aimlessly to attack. The less HP the user has, the greater the move's power.
Flame Burst はじけるほのお The user attacks the target with a bursting flame. The bursting flame damages Pokémon next to the target as well.
Flame Charge ニトロチャージ Cloaking itself in flame, the user attacks. Then, building up more power, the user raises its Speed stat.
Flame Wheel かえんぐるま The user cloaks itself in fire and charges at the target. This may also leave the target with a burn.
Flamethrower かえんほうしゃ The target is scorched with an intense blast of fire. This may also leave the target with a burn.
Flare Blitz [5] フレアドライブ The user cloaks itself in fire and charges the target. This also damages the user quite a lot. This may leave the target with a burn.
Flash フラッシュ The user flashes a bright light that cuts the target's accuracy. It can also be used to illuminate dark caves.
Flash Cannon [5] ラスターカノン The user gathers all its light energy and releases it at once. This may also lower the target's Sp. Def stat.
Flatter おだてる Flattery is used to confuse the target. However, this also raises the target's Sp. Atk stat.
Fling [6] なげつける The user flings its held item at the target to attack. This move's power and effects depend on the item.
Flower Shield フラワーガード The user raises the Defense stat of all Grass-type Pokémon in battle with a mysterious power.
Fly そらをとぶ The user soars and then strikes its target on the next turn. This can also be used to fly to any familiar town.
Flying Press フライングプレス The user dives down onto the target from the sky. This move is Fighting and Flying type simultaneously.
Focus Blast きあいだま The user heightens its mental focus and unleashes its power. This may also lower the target's Sp. Def.

Rototiller たがやす Tilling the soil, the user makes it easier for plants to grow. This raises the Attack and Sp. Atk stats of Grass-type Pokémon.
Round りんしょう The user attacks the target with a song. Others can join in the Round and make the attack do greater damage.
